  <refnamediv>
    <refname>ScriptEvent</refname>

    <refpurpose>Perform a ScriptEvent command</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <synopsis></synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para>The ScriptEvent command allows a user to enter in script within the
    GUI in the mission sequence. This can be useful in a number of ways if its
    easier to enter the script than to use the GUI interface. Also, if
    multiple things needed to be changed rapidly, this could be useful.
    Additionally, the ScriptEvent allows a user to have more freedom if the
    GUI is problematic and won't allow the user to perform the desired
    operation.</para>
  </refsection>

  <refsection>
    <title>Options</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>&lt;Statements&gt;</term>

        <listitem>
          <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
              <term>Default</term>

              <listitem>
                <para>None</para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>

            <varlistentry>
              <term>Limits</term>

              <listitem>
                <para>Any valid line of GMAT script</para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>

            <varlistentry>
              <term>Units</term>

              <listitem>
                <para>None</para>
              </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>

  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>

    <refsection>
      <title>Script Syntax</title>

      <programlisting><code>BeginScript
     &lt;Statements&gt;
EndScript;</code></programlisting>
    </refsection>

    <refsection>
      <title>Script Examples</title>

      <programlisting><code>% Assignment Command inside Script Event

BeginScript
     GMAT testVar = 24;
EndScript;</code></programlisting>
    </refsection>
  </refsection>
